cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.CC

The paper deals with the algebraic properties of rational power series, which are closely related to formal languages and automata theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also involves semirings, which are a fundamental algebraic structure in computer science, and their properties are studied in the context of iteration and Conway semirings. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves some results related to order theory and completeness, which could place it in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Finally, the paper discusses the connection between its results and Kozen's axiomatization of regular languages, which could make it relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
